───────────────────────────────────────────
Definitions
───────────────────────────────────────────

"The Software"
    The original source code, compiled artifacts, and associated documentation
    protected by this License.

"Modification"
    Any addition, deletion, replacement, or rewrite of source code files of
    the Software, including but not limited to: altering existing file content,
    adding new source files that implement business logic, and restructuring
    modules. The following do NOT constitute Modifications:
      · Changes limited to configuration files or environment variables
        (see Section 2);
      · Referencing the Software as an unmodified dependency (e.g. via git
        submodule or package manager);
      · Files automatically generated by the Software at runtime (logs,
        caches, database files, etc.).

"Derivative Work"
    Any work that incorporates a Modification, regardless of form — source
    code, compiled artifact, container image, server-side deployment, or any
    other form.

"Public Release"
    Making source code available in a manner accessible to any person without
    discriminatory restriction.

"Copyright Holder"
    The original author(s) of the Software, or any successor(s) expressly
    authorized in writing by the original author(s).

───────────────────────────────────────────
Section 1  Core Obligation: Modify Means Disclose
───────────────────────────────────────────

If you create a Derivative Work, you must fulfill the following obligations
regardless of whether it is publicly distributed, commercially deployed,
network-served, or used solely for personal or internal purposes:

  1. Make the complete source code of the Derivative Work publicly available
     under a license that satisfies the requirements of Section 3.

  2. Public Release must satisfy at least one of the following:
     a) Publish on a publicly and continuously accessible code hosting
        platform (e.g. GitHub, GitLab, Gitea, etc.);
     b) Accompany every copy of the Derivative Work with its complete
        source code;
     c) Provide a written offer, valid for no less than three years after
        the last distribution or use of the Derivative Work, to supply
        the complete source code to any party upon request at no charge.

  3. Public Release must occur no later than the moment the Derivative Work
     is first used or distributed by any person, including yourself.

  4. The publicly released source code must include everything necessary to
     build and run the Derivative Work — build scripts, dependency manifests,
     and compilation instructions — excluding content exempt under Section 2.

───────────────────────────────────────────
Section 2  Exemption for User Configuration
───────────────────────────────────────────

The following are exempt from the disclosure obligation in Section 1:

  1. Configuration files: Files created or modified solely to adapt the
     Software to a specific runtime environment, including but not limited
     to files containing API keys, access credentials, service endpoints,
     personal preferences, or environment variables (e.g. .env, config.yaml,
     settings.json, and similar files).

  2. User data: Data files, database files, and other user-generated content
     produced, written, or managed by the Software during normal operation.

  3. Test of exemption: A change qualifies if its sole purpose is to adapt
     the Software to a specific runtime environment or personal use case,
     without materially altering the Software's logic, functionality, or
     structure. In cases of ambiguity, interpretation should favor the
     protection of user privacy.

This exemption does not apply to any modification of the Software's core
source code, including but not limited to program logic, algorithms, module
structure, and user interface code.

───────────────────────────────────────────
Section 3  Copyleft
───────────────────────────────────────────

When distributing a Derivative Work, you must satisfy all of the following:

  1. The Derivative Work must be licensed under this License (MSDL v1.0),
     or a later version expressly endorsed by the Copyright Holder. No
     additional restrictions may be imposed.

  2. The Derivative Work must retain all copyright notices, author
     attributions, and the full text of this License from the original
     Software. None may be removed or obscured.

  3. If the Derivative Work adds new author attributions, they must be
     clearly distinguished from the original copyright notices to avoid
     confusion.

  4. Each downstream recipient of the Derivative Work automatically receives
     the same rights directly from the Copyright Holder as you received.
     You may not impose restrictions on their exercise of those rights beyond
     what this License permits.

───────────────────────────────────────────
Section 4  Unmodified Use
───────────────────────────────────────────

If you use, run, or distribute the Software in its original, unmodified
form, the obligations of Section 1 do not apply. You must, however, retain
the full text of this License and all original copyright notices.

